modules.description: Provides functions to spawn and manage lightweight threads, handle asynchronous I/O, and coordinate communication between parallel tasks. Operates with Lwt's domain and thread structures, enabling non-blocking execution and concurrency. Used to implement scalable network servers and parallel data processing pipelines.

Provides functions to schedule computations in parallel domains, returning results as promises, and to execute code in the main domain. Operates with pools of domains and functions that take a single argument. Used to offload CPU-bound tasks to separate domains while maintaining Lwt concurrency, and to safely interact with the main domain from detached computations.
